<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 9:28AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A LINE OF SHOWERS WITH GUSTY WINDS WILL AFFECT WESTERN
APPOMATTOX...EASTERN ROCKBRIDGE...CAMPBELL...EASTERN
BEDFORD...NORTHWESTERN BUCKINGHAM...AND AMHERST COUNTIES...THE CITY
OF BUENA VISTA AND THE CITY OF LYNCHBURG...
At 925 AM EDT, radar indicated showers with gusty winds were located
along a line extending from near Naola to near Bedford. Movement was
northeast at 45 mph.
Winds in excess of 50 mph are possible with these showers.
Locations impacted include...
Lynchburg...
Buena Vista...
Bedford...
Altavista...
Amherst...
Glasgow...
and Brookneal.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
